data.name: Savory Herb-Crusted Salmon with Quinoa and Roasted Vegetables

ingredients.name: Mixed seasonal vegetables (zucchini, bell peppers, carrots)

data.quickTastyDescription: A succulent salmon fillet, herb-crusted and served with a medley of roasted seasonal vegetables for a nutritious and protein-packed meal.
detailedCookingInstructions: In a small bowl, mix olive oil, minced garlic, lemon juice, chopped dill, parsley, salt, and black pepper to create a herb marinade.
Place the salmon fillet on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper and spread the herb marinade evenly over the top.
Arrange the mixed seasonal vegetables and cherry tomatoes around the salmon on the baking sheet, drizzling them with a little olive oil, salt, and pepper.
Bake in the preheated oven for 15-20 minutes, or until the salmon is cooked through and flakes easily with a fork.
Serve hot, garnished with fresh herbs, and enjoy your high-protein meal.
